<div class="s2"><img src="/img/people/HThimbleby.jpg" alt="Harold Thimbleby" align="right" style="border: solid thin black;"/><h1>Library: Harold Thimbleby</h1><small>Peter Ladkin, Harold Thimbleby &laquo;<a href="/lib/aht05.html">Comments on a paper by Voas, Payne & Cohen: “A model for detecting the existence of software corruption in real time”</a>&raquo; <img src="/img/sum.gif" alt="[TeX]"/>[<a href="/lib/?show_abstract=aht05">Abstract</a>] 14.49Kb <span class="note">10131 hits</span></small><br/><small> &laquo;<a href="/lib/aht06.html">Can Viruses Ever Be Useful?</a>&raquo;[<a href="/lib/?show_abstract=aht06">Abstract</a>] 13.87Kb <span class="note">5840 hits</span></small><br/><small> &laquo;<a href="/lib/aht03.html">An organisational solution to piracy and viruses</a>&raquo;[<a href="/lib/?show_abstract=aht03">Abstract</a>] 39.15Kb <span class="note">10974 hits</span></small><br/><small>Harold Thimbleby, Stuart Anderson, Paul Cairns &laquo;<a href="/lib/aht01.html">A framework for modelling trojans and computer virus infection</a>&raquo;[<a href="/lib/?show_abstract=aht01">Abstract</a>] 93.57Kb <span class="note">13782 hits</span></small><br/><small>Harold Thimbleby, Stuart Anderson, Paul Cairns &laquo;<a href="/lib/aht02.html">Reply to `Comment on "A Framework for Modelling Trojans and Computer Virus Infection"' by E. M&auml;kinen</a>&raquo;[<a href="/lib/?show_abstract=aht02">Abstract</a>] 11.41Kb <span class="note">11077 hits</span></small><br/><small>Harold Thimbleby, Ian Witten, David Pullinger &laquo;<a href="/lib/aht00.html">Concepts of cooperation in artificial life</a>&raquo; <img src="/img/sum.gif" alt="[TeX]"/>[<a href="/lib/?show_abstract=aht00">Abstract</a>] 41.9Kb <span class="note">11957 hits</span></small><br/><small>Ian Witten, Harold Thimbleby &laquo;<a href="/lib/aht04.html">The worm that turned: A social use of computer viruses</a>&raquo;[<a href="/lib/?show_abstract=aht04">Abstract</a>] 29.76Kb <span class="note">11974 hits</span></small><br/><p>Harold published his first paper, on menu selection, in 1978, and has since written nearly 400 publications - of which nearly 200 were invited - from newspaper articles to articles in Encyclopedia Britannica, as well as many refereed research publications. He wrote User Interface Design, published in the ACM Press Frontier Series in 1990.</p>
<p>Press On book cover His fifth book, Press On, was published by MIT Press in November 2007.</p>
<p>He was a Royal Society-Wolfson Research Merit Award Holder. He was 28th Gresham Professor of Geometry. He was awarded the British Computer Society Wilkes Medal, and won a Toshiba Year of Invention prize. He is a visiting professor at UCL and at Middlesex University.</p>Homepage <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.cs.swan.ac.uk/~csharold/">http://www.cs.swan.ac.uk/~csharold/</a><br clear="all"/></div>
